FILE anes2008_2009panel_fcodebook.txt
-------------------------
Complete Release of the
ANES 2008-2009 Panel Study Frequency codebook
VERSION 20090903 (September 03, 2010)



FREQUENCY CODEBOOK FOR THE COMPLETE RELEASE OF THE 
ANES 2008-2009 PANEL STUDY



CONTENTS
-------------------------
1. NOTE ON DOCUMENTATION
2. NOTE TO USERS OF SPSS PORTABLE (.por) FILES
3. VARIABLE FREQUENCIES



>> 1. NOTE ON DOCUMENTATION

The primary documentation of the Panel Study Complete Release 
is contained in the "Methodology Report and User's Guide for 
the ANES 2008-2009 Panel Study". That guide is availble on the 
ANES web site www.electionstudies.org) in PDF format.

This Frequency Codebook lists the variable names, labels, 
codes, and frequencies for the numeric, non-continuous 
variables on the data file.

Please see the Methodology Report for more documentation.


>> 2. NOTE TO USERS OF SPSS PORTABLE (.por) FILES

Users of the SPSS portable (.por) file for this Advance
Release dataset will encounter some variables with
abbreviated versions of variable names, as indicated below.  
String variables with values having length greater than 256 
characters are also truncated in the .por release file.
These limitations are inherent to .por file structure.

Note that the unweighted distributions below were not produced 
from the release SPSS portable file.

Users of SPSS data (.sav) files will not encounter these
shorter variable names.
